<TITLE> Land gets pricier from Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)Land in metropolitan areas is becoming pricier from Tuesday. Law minister Shafiq Ahmed said on Monday the government has increased land prices in all city corporations and district towns. Registration fees, stamp fees and local government taxes, however, have been cut for the next three years. The land prices have shot up between two-and-a-half and four times in big cities and towns effective from Sept 1, the minister said in a news conference. The prices have shot up two and a half to four times in the big cities and towns effective from Sept 1 (Tuesday), the minister said at a news conference. "The land prices, however, in the mofussil or at upazila level have not seen any increase and registration fees, stamp fees and local government taxes have been slashed for the next three years," he said. The prices of land at district headquarters level have been increased two-and-a-half times, he said. For Sylhet, Rajshahi, Khulna and Barisal city corporations, the increases have been threefold and in case of Dhaka and Chittagong city corporations, the prices have been upscaled fourfold. Of the district headquarters, Bogra, Narayanganj and Gazipur are to see land prices increased three times. Besides, Tongi, Savar and Keraniganj will see the land prices increased threefold again. bdne
